<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="285" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,353,740]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,305,353,380]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species is relatively common throughout the northern GOM. Commonly reported as a coastal species inhabiting shallow waters from the shore out to approximately 
<quantity box="[961,1021,390,416]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" unit="m" value="30.0">30 m</quantity>
, although individuals of this species have been documented during NMFS SEFSC trawl surveys out to approximately 
<quantity box="[1065,1122,426,452]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" unit="m" value="90.0">90 m</quantity>
depth.
</paragraph>
